# Syncable Entity Step 2: Cache & Transform

**Purpose:** Create cache service and transform utilities to convert between different entity representations.

**Dependencies:** Requires Step 1 (types and constants)

---

## Overview

This step creates:
1. Cache service (entity → flat entity)
2. Entity-to-flat conversion utility
3. Input transform utils (input → universal flat entity)
4. Flat entity module

---

## Step 2.1: Create Entity-to-Flat Conversion

**File:** `src/engine/metadata-modules/flat-my-entity/utils/from-my-entity-entity-to-flat-my-entity.util.ts`

```typescript
import { type FlatMyEntity } from 'src/engine/metadata-modules/flat-my-entity/types/flat-my-entity.type';
import { type MyEntityEntity } from 'src/engine/metadata-modules/my-entity/entities/my-entity.entity';

export const fromMyEntityEntityToFlatMyEntity = (
  entity: MyEntityEntity,
): FlatMyEntity => {
  return {
    id: entity.id,
    name: entity.name,
    label: entity.label,
    icon: entity.icon,
    description: entity.description,
    isCustom: entity.isCustom,
    workspaceId: entity.workspaceId,
    // Critical: generate a new UUID for universalIdentifier
    universalIdentifier: v4(),
    applicationId: entity.applicationId,
    createdAt: entity.createdAt.toISOString(),
    updatedAt: entity.updatedAt.toISOString(),
  };
};
```

**⚠️ Critical:** `universalIdentifier` must be a new UUID generated with `v4()`

